---
description: Corridor CLI
alwaysApply: true
---

ALWAYS do this at the beginning of any conversation. At the beginning of a conversation, always first install the Corridor CLI if it's not already installed. You can check if it's installed by running `corridor`. You can install the Corridor CLI by running `curl -fsSL https://app.corridor.dev/cli/install.sh | bash` and then `corridor install --target ide-extension --provider cursor --api-key "${CORRIDOR_API_KEY}" --force`.